com.example.lab_net

Class plotLocFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
      • com.example.lab_net.plotLocFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, androidx.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, androidx.savedstate.SavedStateRegistryOwner

    public class plotLocFragment
extends androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
    plotLocFragment loads up Google Map and gets location coordinates of all trials of an experiment based on experiment ID from plotLocActivity,and plots all coordinates on map for user to see. If location coordinates are not available then user is informed via toasts.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    gurjogsingh
    See Also:
    plotLocActivity
